HTTP

    http-client.pl and http-server.pl are small programs which demonstrate
    basic socket handling in Pugs.

    http-client.pl fetches an URL using HTTP/1.0,
    http-server.pl is a small HTTP/1.0 server.

    Note: The functions concerning threading used in http-server.pl are not yet
    specced.

IRC

    bot_irc.pl is a simplistic IRC bot.

    hangmanbot.pl, logbot.pl, seenbot.pl, svnbot.pl, and evalbot/ all use the
    Net::IRC framework.

    hangmanbot.pl allows you to play Hangman over IRC.
    logbot.pl     is a simplistic IRC logger, which outputs illoger2 compatible
                  logfiles.
    seenbot.pl    is a small bot answering "?seen nick" questions.
    svnbot.pl     relays the latest Subversion commits to IRC.
                  svnbot6 is used on irc.freenode.net's #perl6 and
                  irc.perl.org's #parrot, see svnbot.pl's POD for more
                  information.
    evalbot/      is a bot which eval()s Perl 6 commands, see evalbot/README
                  for more information.

Miscellaneous

    screen-nodestatus.pl is a handy utility for GNU screen(1) users. Using it,
    screen can display the status of selected hosts in its statusline. See the
    sourcecode of screen-nodestatus.pl for installation instructions and a
    screenshot.
